[20260512-132703.1850]  
[20260512-132703.1850]  Converts from four possible input bases (including 10), to 29 possible output
[20260512-132703.1867]  bases. Strictly positional notation conversion, not for binary-to-text
[20260512-132703.1883]  encoding/decoding. (Though you can use the same common 2^N encoding bases such
[20260512-132703.1900]  as base32 or base64, as positional notation.)
[20260512-132703.1911]  
[20260512-132703.1912]  Syntax: convert-base-v1b  [optional args]  <NUMBER>  <OBASE>
[20260512-132703.1925]    Required arguments (in any order):
[20260512-132703.1933]      <NUMBER> .........: The input value to convert
[20260512-132703.1944]      <OBASE> ..........: The base to convert to (default 10 if not specified)
[20260512-132703.1960]    Optional arguments:
[20260512-132703.1966]      --ibase <base> ...: The input base (default 10 if not specified)
[20260512-132703.1981]      --from  <base> ...: Alias for '--ibase'
[20260512-132703.1991]      --obase <base> ...: Optional explicit flag for output base.
[20260512-132703.2005]      --to  <base> .....: Alias for '--obase'
[20260512-132703.2015]      --lcase ..........: Lower case (for bases with alpha and only one case)
[20260512-132703.2031]      --clipin .........: Use clipboard for input
[20260512-132703.2041]      --clipout ........: Use clipboard for output
[20260512-132703.2053]      --silent .........: No CLI output. Also sets --clipout.
[20260512-132703.2071]      --help, --about, --version [or -h, -a, -v]
[20260512-132703.2081]    Valid values for output <base>
[20260512-132703.2088]      Note: ST=Standard, PS=Pseudostandard, PUB=Published, C=Custom:
[20260512-132703.2103]          2      ST  aka Binary ................. 0,1
[20260512-132703.2115]          8      ST  aka Octal .................. 0-7
[20260512-132703.2125]         10      ST  aka Decimal [default] ...... 0-9
[20260512-132703.2137]         16      ST  aka Hexedecimal ............ 0-9, A-F
[20260512-132703.2149]         26      PS  One-case alphabetic ........ A-Z
[20260512-132703.2161]         32[r]   ST  RFC 4648 §6 ................ A-Z, 2-7
[20260512-132703.2175]         32h     ST  RFC 4648 §7, 'Base32Hex' ... 0-9, A-V
[20260512-132703.2186]         32c     PUB Crockford's Base32 ......... 0-9, A-Z no I, L, O, U
[20260512-132703.2211]         32ws    PUB Word-safe Base32 ........... 2-9, CFGHJMPQRVWX, cfghjmpqrvwx
[20260512-132703.2228]         36      PS  Just alphanum .............. 0-9, A-Z
[20260512-132703.2241]         38host  C   Valid *nix host and domain name characters
[20260512-132703.2255]         39user  C   Valid *nix username characters
[20260512-132703.2265]         45email C   Valid HTML5 <email> address characters
[20260512-132703.2279]         48jc1ws C   Base 32ws + unicode symbols
[20260512-132703.2289]         52      PS  Both-case alphabetic ....... A-Z, a-z
[20260512-132703.2301]         62      PS  All alphanum ............... 0-9, A-Z, a-z
[20260512-132703.2315]         64[r]   ST  RFC 4648 §4 ................ A-Z, a-z, 0-9, +, /
[20260512-132703.2329]         64u     ST  RFC 4648 §5, URL-safe ...... A-Z, a-z, 0-9, -, _
[20260512-132703.2344]         64h     PS  Hex like, URL-safe ......... 0-9, A-Z, a-z, -, _
[20260512-132703.2360]         64jc1   C   Base 62, +2 unicode symbols  0-9, A-Z, a-z, ʞ, λ
[20260512-132703.2375]         64jc1ws C   Base 48jcw + more unicode symbols
[20260512-132703.2386]        128jc1ws C   Base 64jcw + more unicode symbols
[20260512-132703.2399]        128jc1   C   Base 64jc  + more unicode symbols
[20260512-132703.2409]        256jc1   C   Base 128jc + more unicode symbols
[20260512-132703.2421]        288jc1   C   Base 256jc + more unicode symbols
[20260512-132703.2432]      v1 backwards-compatiable 'incongruous' word-safe bases:
[20260512-132703.2446]         48v1compat, 64v1compat, 128v1compat
[20260512-132703.2455]    Valid values for --ibase:
[20260512-132703.2462]      2, 8, 10, 16, 36
